    "context": "The LLM-as-a-judge approach introduces several known biases that evaluator designers must account for. Verbosity bias causes judges to prefer longer responses even when shorter ones are more accurate. Position bias leads judges to favor responses presented first in a comparison. Self-enhancement bias occurs when an LLM rates its own outputs higher than those from other models. Mitigating these biases requires techniques like randomizing response order, using multiple judge models, and calibrating against human annotations."
}
